check_topology is a Nagios plugin to check for the correct configuration of the hosts' parents.

For each defined host in the supplied hosts.cfg Nagios configuration file check_topology checks
if the last hop in the network path corresponds to the defined parent.

Usage: check_topology [options] -c conf

  -c conf     hosts.cfg file
  -h          help screen
  -x          exclude hosts
  -v          increase verbosity
  -V          prints version information

Example: ./check_topology -c /etc/nagios/hosts.cfg -x somehost -v -v

Requirements:
- lft: layer four traceroute (http://pwhois.org/lft/index.who)
